Alumni volunteers offered pep talks near a coffee station, and career counselors assisted in identifying applicable industries. Small groups analyzed recruiter enthusiasm and quietly rehearsed elevator pitches against the wall. Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel on technical interview preparation occurred in adjoining classrooms, alongside a cybersecurity company conducting a password cracking challenge on a laptop. Exhibitors included consulting firms, healthcare providers showcasing community outreach photos, and a robotics startup flying a small drone above its booth. As the final hour approached, marked by announcement chimes, students filled out interview sign-up sheets before leaving with tote bags.

Concurrently, in an adjoining classroom, workshops on networking etiquette take place where career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops and small groups analyze which recruiters appeared most enthusiastic. A whiteboard in the classroom lists employers scheduling same-day interviews, and recruiters remind students to follow up with personalized emails. Announcement chimes signal the final hour of the fair, while international students queue for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. A cybersecurity company is also conducting a password cracking challenge on a laptop.

Career center staff assist international students with advice on visa sponsorship requirements while logging attendance metrics on laptops. Workshops on networking etiquette are held in an adjoining classroom, with small groups analyzing recruiter enthusiasm and a whiteboard displaying employers scheduling same-day interviews. A cybersecurity company conducts a password cracking challenge, while a robotics startup flies a small drone above its booth. As the final hour approaches, announcement chimes signal the closing phase, and monitors near the exit display a post-event survey link, with the aroma of coffee and catered snacks wafting from the lounge.

Alumni volunteers offered pep talks near a coffee station, while career counselors assisted students in identifying applicable industries and visa sponsorship requirements for international attendees. Small groups analyzed recruiter enthusiasm and quietly rehearsed elevator pitches against the wall. Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel on technical interview preparation took place in adjoining classrooms, alongside a cybersecurity company conducting a password cracking challenge on a laptop. Exhibitors included consulting firms and healthcare providers showcasing community outreach photos, with a robotics startup flying a small drone above its booth. As the final hour approached, marked by announcement chimes, students filled out interview sign-up sheets before leaving with tote bags.

Human resources teams jot notes on tablets while students introduce themselves. Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel discussing preparation for technical interviews take place in an adjoining classroom, where career center staff log attendance metrics on laptops. International students queue for advice on visa sponsorship requirements. A robotics startup attracts attention with a small drone flying above its booth, while a cybersecurity company conducts a password cracking challenge on a laptop. As the final hour approaches, announcement chimes signal the closing phase of the fair, and monitors near the exit display a post-event survey link. Students exit with tote bags filled with notebooks, pens, and stacks of business cards, while the air is filled with the scent of coffee and catered snacks.
